Add a comprehensive metrics and monitoring system. Create `src/metrics.js` with the following: 1) `metrics.counter(name, labels)` - creates a counter metric that can be incremented with `counter.inc(labels, value)` and retrieved with `counter.get(labels)`. 2) `metrics.gauge(name, labels)` - creates a gauge metric that can be set with `gauge.set(labels, value)` and retrieved with `gauge.get(labels)`. 3) `metrics.histogram(name, labels, buckets)` - creates a histogram with configurable buckets (default: [0.1, 0.5, 1, 2, 5, 10] seconds) that can observe values with `histogram.observe(labels, value)` and get statistics with `histogram.get(labels)`. 4) `metrics.timer(name, labels)` - convenience wrapper around histogram for timing operations, returns a function that when called stops the timer. 5) Built-in metrics collection: (a) 'nodejs_memory_heap_used_bytes' - gauge tracking heap usage, (b) 'nodejs_eventloop_lag_seconds' - histogram tracking event loop lag, (c) 'forever_operations_total' - counter tracking total operations performed, (d) 'forever_operation_duration_seconds' - histogram tracking operation durations. 6) `metrics.getSnapshot()` - returns all metrics in Prometheus text format for easy scraping. 7) `metrics.reset()` - resets all metrics to initial state. 8) `metrics.exportJSON()` - returns all metrics as JSON object. 9) Write tests in `tests/metrics.test.js`. 10) Export from `src/index.js`. 11) Add `forever metrics` CLI subcommand that displays current metrics in a formatted table. 12) Integrate with health system to expose basic metrics via the health endpoint.